Athena is a set of virtual health solutions designed to reduce the risk of depression and diabetes in individuals at risk of these conditions. The key features of the Athena mobile platform include:

1. recognize symptoms of common mental disorders (including but not limited to depression, anxiety-related disorders, psychosis) using AI algorithms based on an evolving, extensive library of psychiatric symptoms according to the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual for Mental Disorders the fifth edition (DSM-5);

2. integrate health data from iOS Health Kit, Care Kit, and Google Fit;

3. self-report assessments for stress, depression, and anxiety;

4. provide users access to real time coaching and/or treatment from certified health professionals based on their health data;

5. self-help interactive micro-lessons aimed at a. providing individuals with information about diabetes and common mental health problems; and b. practical evidence-based strategies designed to manage these conditions;

6. complete and track progress of lessons at your own pace;

7. allow individuals to consult with certified health professionals in real time on a range of health issues;

8. personalised notifications to drive users‚Äô engagement and compliance with treatment.

Note: Athena is a customizable health solution platform aimed at providing cost-effective digital health solutions in partnership with enterprises, organizations, and health industry partners. Our clients include certified health professionals (including but not limited to general practitioners, medical specialists, and allied health professionals) who are licensed to practice in their respective countries. Athena Pty Ltd is a health technology company headquartered in Australia.  For further queries please contact us at info@athenaailab.com/support@athenaailab.com.
